\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zwb1665702684890.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zwb1665702684890.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zwb1665702684890.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zwb1665702684890\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n           \n Uniface Web Applications\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"zwb1665702684890__uniface_web_applications_67303\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface web applications run in a Uniface Web Application Server and are invoked by the client browser over the internet.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zwb1665702684890__p_d19775e1_d19776e1_d19777e1\">To start a Uniface web application, the user uses a supported web browser to go to the URL of the main component. The URL specifies the web server and the requested component, which may be a Dynamic Server Page (DSP) or Static Server Page (USP).</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zwb1665702684890__p_d19778e1_d19779e1_d19780e1\">The user interface of these applications is provided by dynamic and/or static server page components, which generate and update HTML pages. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ull1704691217498.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ull1704691217498.html\" title=\"Dynamic Server Pages(DSP) components define the user interface of web pages that can be incrementally and dynamically updated. They can be used in rich interactive web applications and in cross-platform mobile apps.\">Dynamic Server Pages</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"snh1704692180687.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/snh1704692180687.html\" title=\"Static Server Page (USP) components generate a complete web page every time they are activated. This makes them useful for relatively static web pages or a thin-client architecture in which all processing is done on the server. They can also be used for RESTful applications or file upload functionality.\">Static Server Pages</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zwb1665702684890__p_d19781e1_d19782e1_d19783e1\">Other application processing can be provided by service components that are activated by DSPs and USPs.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ods1692009951805.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Applications</a><p>Uniface applications are typically mission-critical enterprise applications that use and maintain data stored in one or more databases, files, or other data resources. They may integrate with all kinds of non-Uniface applications, and they can be deployed on a wide variety of platforms.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tuz1665702667344.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Web Application Server</a><p>The Uniface Web Application Server (WASV) handles server-side processing for web and mobile applications.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xax1665702683800.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface HTTP Processing</a><p>HTTP is an internet protocol that provides a way for a client to send a request to a server and for the server to return a response. It is used in web applications, mobile apps, and web services to transfer data in a defined request-response cycle. This topic describes how HTTP is used in Uniface applications.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534648\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534648\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface Web Applications Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface Web Applications Uniface web applications run in a Uniface Web Application Server and are invoked by the client browser over the internet. To start a Uniface web application, the user uses a supported web browser to go to the URL of the main component. The URL specifies the web server and the requested component, which may be a Dynamic Server Page (DSP) or Static Server Page (USP). The user interface of these applications is provided by dynamic and/or static server page components, which generate and update HTML pages. For more information, see Dynamic Server Pages and Static Server Pages . Other application processing can be provided by service components that are activated by DSPs and USPs. Related Links Uniface Applications Uniface applications are typically mission-critical enterprise applications that use and maintain data stored in one or more databases, files, or other data resources. They may integrate with all kinds of non-Uniface applications, and they can be deployed on a wide variety of platforms. Web Application Server The Uniface Web Application Server (WASV) handles server-side processing for web and mobile applications. Uniface HTTP Processing HTTP is an internet protocol that provides a way for a client to send a request to a server and for the server to return a response. It is used in web applications, mobile apps, and web services to transfer data in a defined request-response cycle. This topic describes how HTTP is used in Uniface applications. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}